org.jsapar.schema

Class FixedWidthSchemaLine

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jsapar.schema.SchemaLine
      • org.jsapar.schema.FixedWidthSchemaLine
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable

    public class FixedWidthSchemaLine
extends SchemaLine
    This class represents the schema for a line of a fixed with file. Each cell within the line has a specified size. There are no delimiter characters.
    Author:
    stejon0

        public FixedWidthSchemaLine(int nOccurs)
        Creates an empty schema line which will occur nOccurs times within the file. When the line has occured nOccurs times this schema-line will not be used any more.
        Parameters:
        nOccurs - The number of times this schema line is used while parsing or writing.

      • FixedWidthSchemaLine

      • getMinLength

        public int getMinLength()
        Returns:
        the minimal length of a line to generate. If the sum of all cells' length do not reach the length of a line, the line will be filled with the fill character.

      • setMinLength

        public void setMinLength(int length)
        The minimal length of a line to generate. If the sum of all cells' length do not reach the length of a line, the line will be filled with the fill character. Use the method addFillerCellToReachMinLength() to make sure that minLength is also used while reading.
        Parameters:
        length - the length to set
